Furthermore, coal is considered the current and the future fuel in India, where there are total reserves of approximately 150 gigatons. Thus, the IGCC process along with carbon capture looks crucial. In terms of coal reserves, India comes third globally after the USA and Russia as first and second (Ashkanani et al. 2020). Globally, coal is the largest energy source for electricity generation and the second-largest feedstock source of primary energy (Wei et al. 2020). However, with the current rate of CO2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
