				\begin{document}$$\hbox {CO}_{2}$$\end{document} of flue gases. This procedure demands the utilisation of photosynthetic organisms (microalgae) for anthropogenic carbon capture and storage. Marine microalgae have been proposed to be of more prominent potential because they have more distinguished carbon stabilisation rates than land plants (Ben-Mansour et al. 2016). Microalgal culturing is very costly; however, the technique creates different composites of high worth that can be utilised for income production. Microalgal photosynthesis further commands to precipitation of calcium carbonate that can aid as an enduring sink for carbon (Nakamura and Senior 2005).

The separation based on membranes substances depends on the variances in the interactions that occurred within gases and the materials of the membrane, that adjusted to permit several pieces to transfer discriminatory into the membrane (Li et al. 2011c). Membranes have extraordinary merit in CO2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
