The chemical or reactive absorbents comprise amines, blends, ionic liquids, aqueous solvents, ammonia, etc. The blends were then created to merge the positive features of diverse absorbents, and concurrently overcoming their negative features. The physical absorbents comprise solvents like Rectisol, Selexol, etc. To be applied as an absorbent, a solvent should possess the required features such as exceptional reactivity and absorptivity with CO2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
