				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned}&\mathrm {nCO}+2 \mathrm {nH}_{2} \leftrightarrow \left( -\mathrm {CH}_{2}-\right) \mathrm {n}+\mathrm {nH}_{2} \mathrm {O} \;\;\;\;\;\; \Delta \mathrm {H}_{\mathrm {r} 298 \mathrm {K}}^{\circ }=-\,\mathrm {n} * 152\,\mathrm {kJ}/\mathrm {mol} \end{aligned}$$\end{document}The produced hydrocarbons are segregated from non-reacted feed and gaseous hydrocarbons, and after that, they can be upgraded via undergoing of hydrocracking and isomerisation (Piermartini et al. 2017).

sec.title:
Production of biofuel (green fuel) using CO2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
