sec.p:
In contrast to traditional fuels, biofuels derived from renewable sources are ultimately the best appropriate choice given its environment and economic benefits (Santamaría and Azqueta 2015). Algae are a promising green energy source due to their high protein and oil content. Conversion of algal biomass into biofuel was successfully implemented as shown in Fig. 24. Atmospheric carbon, either inorganic or organic origin, can be fixed using different algal species (Singh and Olsen 2011). Successful absorption of CO2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
